3 N.(1) Except as provided in Paragraph (2) of this Subsection, in addition to
4 all other forms of compensation which are authorized for assessors by the provisions
5 of this Section, the annual compensation for each assessor shall be increased by five
6 percent annually through calendar year 2029. The additional compensation
7 authorized by this Subsection shall become effective only if the assessor publishes
8 notice of intent to increase his compensation on two separate days in the official
9 journal of the parish in which the assessor's office is situated. The last day of
10 publication of the notice shall be at least thirty days prior to the date that the assessor
11 increases his compensation.
12 (2) No assessor who, for any taxable year ending after December 31, 2025,
13 assesses property in violation of the exemption provided in R.S. 47:6001 shall be
14 eligible for any compensation increase authorized by Paragraph (1) of this
15 Subsection.
16 Section 2. The intent of this Act is to authorize for each assessor four compensation
17 increases, in the number of one increase per year, during the 2026, 2027, 2028, and 2029
18 calendar years unless prohibited by the provisions of this Act.
19 Section 3. This Act shall become effective on July 1, 2026; if vetoed by the governor
20 and subsequently approved by the legislature, this Act shall become effective on July 1,
21 2026, or on the day following such approval by the legislature, whichever is later.
